I worked a summer job at an amusement park during college.  Many people could not get onto the rides and buckle themselves in.  I have seen many angry people drive badly.<br>
<br>
Should I assume by this that all people are stupid and bad drivers?<br>
<br>
I believe that many people come here for a better life.  I lived in South Florida for many years and watched the Cuban community there change Miami.<br>
<br>
Now are there problems, particularly in California, with immigration policy?  Yes.<br>
<br>
I have met good and bad of all races, creeds and colors.  I have not understood some of the cultural things (still have a problem with the caste system).<br>
<br>
By the way, I don't buy the &quot;they do jobs white folks won't do&quot; arguement.  One of the jobs most often cited is farm worker.  I grew up in the Northeast and not too many Mexicans were doing farm work.  But agriculture was the number 2 industry in the state of New York (after Tourism).  Who was doing all that work?<br>
